  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hyperpronation is af frequent cause of excessive load in foot and crus. Pain and limited
      functional ability cause problems with work-related activities, sport activities and leisure
      activities.

      There are only few studies of the frequency of pain related to hyperpronation in foot and the
      effect of exercises. Medics and physiotherapists need sufficient evidence-based knowledge to
      treat these patients correctly.

      Therefore, the investigators want to study the effect of exercises and inner soles for
      treatment of patients with chronic pain and hyperpronation of foot.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
